ViraAI Modular Backend Environment Variables (FastAPI)

------------------------------------

1. FastAPI Settings

------------------------------------

SECRET_KEY: Used for signing JWT tokens (authentication).

IMPORTANT: Change this to a long, random string in the actual .env file.

SECRET_KEY="YOUR_JWT_SECRET_KEY_HERE"
ALGORITHM="HS256"

------------------------------------

2. Database Connection (PostgreSQL)

------------------------------------

Note: In the Docker Compose setup, 'db' is the service name acting as the hostname.

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgrespassword@db:5432/viraai_db"

------------------------------------

3. AI Service Keys (For the AI Worker Service)

------------------------------------

Your API key for Google Gemini model access

GEMINI_API_KEY="your_gemini_api_key_here"

Your API token for HuggingFace models

HF_API_TOKEN="your_huggingface_api_token_here"

------------------------------------

4. CORS Settings (Frontend Address)

------------------------------------

IMPORTANT: This must include all origins allowed to access the API.

'http://localhost:3000' is for local development.

'https://www.google.com/search?q=https://viraai.io' is for the production domain.

CORS_ORIGINS="http://localhost:3000,https://www.google.com/search?q=https://viraai.io"
